But the carnival of transfers does not end there.
Almost three billion was lost in the budget for various compensation to victims of communism and crimes, or for expenses for litigation, even for building savings.
Whether the state can do without this money is not certain.
This is a lottery.
If we lose an international dispute, we will have to pay for it anyway, says Janota.
The minister will then have to save money inside the ministry or, in the worst case, tap the government's budget reserve.
One hundred million is also missing for the already launched two-billion project State Treasury, which should allow online monitoring of what individual offices spend on.
The first stage will start in January.
If the finance minister does not find the money elsewhere, the project would have to stop, sanctions will come, warns Janota.
