The subjects of geography and history will be strengthened as part of the reform of the general grammar school, Chatel said.
Education Minister Luc Chatel said in an interview with JDD magazine on Sunday that history and geography subjects will be "strengthened" as part of the reform of general grammar schools, although their teaching will no longer be compulsory in the last year of a grammar school with a focus on exact sciences.
Now all second-year students will have four classes a week, and there will be the same general culture program for all, Chatel confirmed.
