An Ifop poll published Saturday by the daily Humanité showed that seven French out of ten (69%) disagree with the government's project to abolish compulsory history and geography classes in the graduating year with specialization S, which is why many intellectuals and teachers have criticized the abolition, both on the left and some MPs on the right.
