As part of Master's Degree 2 (M2), they will undergo an entrance examination focused on their field at the beginning of the year and another examination at the end of the year to test their ability to teach, the minister explained.
They will participate in professional internships during the second year of the Master's degree and for the first year they will act in front of pupils as a professor-intern.
If you add up all the internships that will be offered to you before the admission process, you will gain more experience with pupils, almost 300 hours, he continued.
